- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper deals with type systems and their representations, which can be seen as a logical framework. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper discusses a specific type system (system M) and proposes a new representation (system S) for it. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is relevant because the paper deals with typing derivations and intersection types. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible because the paper uses some linguistic terminology (e.g. "tracks") to describe the new representation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible because the paper introduces a new data structure (families of types indexed by integers) to represent intersection types.
